Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
readSdpFile(25.10)                                          readSdpFile(25.10)

Name
       readSdpFile  -  Reads in a relative placement file (in .sdp format) and
       then calls placeSdpGroup to place all the structured  data  path  (SDP)
       elements defined in the file

Syntax
       readSdpFile

       [-help]

       -file <file_name>

       [-hierPath <path>]

       [-leftoverGroup]

       [-origin <llx ><lly>]

       [-skipPlacement]

       Reads  in  a  relative  placement  file (in .sdp format) and then calls
       placeSdpGroup to place all the structured data path (SDP) elements  de-
       fined  in  the  file.  If  -skipPlacement  is  specified,  placement is
       skipped.

       If the SDP file refers to an  instance  that  is  not  present  in  the
       netlist  or design, the software issues a warning but continues to load
       the rest of the SDP file.

       Before using readSdpFile, you should have:

              * Imported the design

Parameters
       -help  Outputs a brief description that includes type and  default  in-
              formation for each readSdpFile parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and all of its parame-
              ters, use the man command: man readSdpFile.

       -file <file_name>
              Specifies the name of the input file containing SDP definitions.
              The  SDP  file  format supports wildcards (* and ?) for instance
              names. It also supports numeric bus bit range as part of an  in-
              stance name.

       -hierPath <path>
              Specifies  the hierarchical path name of the SDP elements speci-
              fied in the SDP file. This path name is appended to all SDP  in-
              stances defined in the file.

       -leftoverGroup
              Stores  all remaining instances in the current hierarchical path
              that do not belong to any SDP group into a new SDP group  called
              <SDPname>_LEFTOVER_RPLGRP. An error is issued if a logical hier-
              archy has more than one SDP group.

       -origin <llx> <lly>
              Defines the SDP location by specifying the SDP block origin. The
              origin  information  is applied to all SDPs specified in the SDP
              file.

       -skipPlacement
              Reads in the SDP group definition but does not place the group.

Examples
              * The following command reads the dtmf_chip.sdp file and  places
                all  defined SDP elements. It also appends the specified hier-
                archical path to all elements.

                readSdpFile        -file        dtmf_chip.sdp        -hierPath
                DTMF_CHIP/TDSP_CORE_INST

